-- Wealthy To Face Tax Increased Scrutiny from Tax Office, Australian Reports
-- Rebecca Keenan
-- 2010-07-07T21:09:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/wealthy-to-face-tax-increased-scrutiny-from-tax-office-australian-reports.html

          
          
             The Australian Taxation Office will
scrutinize the finances of more than 360 wealthy Australians
that hold at least A$30 million in assets, the Australian
newspaper reported.  
 People using tax secrecy havens will also face surveillance
under a new compliance program, the newspaper said. The nationâ€™s
biggest tax probe, the Wickenby project, raised A$450 million in
liabilities in 2009-10 of which A$56 million was collected, the
report said.  
